message:
Welcome! Here are some tips based on my experience:
1.  Growth Serum (ğŸŒ¡ï¸): Almost always apply this once to any newly combined item. It reliably increases value. However, applying it a second time often *reduces* the value (e.g., from 25 to 0 or even negative), so be very cautious with repeat applications, especially on items with diverse features.
2.  Mutation Catalyst (ğŸ§¬): Avoid this tool entirely unless your score is already 0 and you have nothing to lose. It consistently leads to heavily negative values, confirming the previous player's hint.
3.  Combining Items: Combining ingredients with similar features (e.g., two land animals or two air animals) often yields a neutral item that can be boosted by 'growth serum'. Combining items with diverse features (e.g., land and water, different sizes) might yield a small positive value, also benefiting from the first 'growth serum' application. Crucially, do NOT combine already grown or super-grown items with each other. This reliably creates highly negative-value 'overcomplicated' items. Stick to combining raw ingredients or using growth serum on simple combined items.
4.  Score Management: Your score cannot drop below 0. Use this to your advantage to experiment with negative-value items if you have a more valuable item securing your score.
